SIMPLE: rhinophore
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rhinophore
<hw>Rhi"no*phore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Rhino-</ets> + Gr. <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the two tentacle-like organs on the back
of the head or neck of a nudibranch or tectibranch mollusk. They are
usually retractile, and often transversely furrowed or plicate, and are
regarded as olfactory organs. Called also <altname>dorsal
tentacles</altname>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Pygobranchia</er>,
and <er>Opisthobranchia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhinoplastic</ent>⟦br⟧
